as no relevant entries, the draft includes a disclaimer rather than fabricating facts.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model behavior under missing-evidence conditions (disclaimer vs hallucination). Mocking generation can trivially return a disclaimer and miss real fabrication failures. Rejected higher level (Workflow): behavior evaluates one model decision under a specific context condition, not a multi-agentic sequence.","test_description":"Provide real threads with intentionally empty/irrelevant KB retrieval results and run the real model; assert disclaimer presence and absence of unsupported factual claims in generated drafts across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The approval workflow blocks sending until the user explicitly approves — no draft is sent automatically.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a state-handoff/orchestration boundary between draft state, approval gate, and send action. A single-function unit test is insufficient if the bug appears when modules are wired. Rejected higher level (System): behavior does not require real SMTP/network/OS semantics to catch; a local sender spy/fake can prove send is blocked until explicit approval.","test_description":"Wire workflow controller + approval state store + send adapter in-process; simulate draft creation and user events, assert send adapter is never called before explicit approve and is called exactly once after approval.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — read thread, generate draft, check facts, present for approval — works end-to-end for a real email thread.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly targets the full agent pipeline and sequential handoffs across stages including real generation. Failures can emerge from cross-step interactions (thread context -> generation -> fact-check outcome -> approval presentation) that lower-level isolated tests miss. Rejected lower level (Agentic): single-step model testing cannot validate end-to-end stage ordering and state propagation across the full sequence.","test_description":"Execute the production-like pipeline on real email-thread inputs with real model calls: ingest thread, generate draft, run fact-check against KB, and present approval UI state; assert correct stage outputs, ordering, and final blocked-until-approval state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.7}}]}
